      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That profound feeling of depletion goes beyond a typical artistic slump; it sounds like significant emotional exhaustion. When the core resource you've been pouring into something feels empty, the grief over that losing integral part of your identity is real and valid. Please consider this not as an end, but as a signal that the focus needs to shift from *creation* to *self-reclamation*. You deserve to tend to the person beneath the maker, even if that means pausing the work entirely for a long time.",
